Ad Text:
Want to bring ideas to life?
Aurecon is a design, engineering and advisory company, but not as you know it!

Drawing on our deep pool of technical and advisory expertise, we co-create innovative solutions with our clients to some of the world's most complex challenges. And through a range of unique creative processes and skills, we work to re-imagine, shape and design a better future.

How will your ideas contribute to shaping what's next?
You'll work with a national team of highly skilled specialists. You'll be a trusted partner to a diverse range of international clients and develop a deep understanding of their challenges to co-create innovative solutions that help shape the future. You will be primarily engaged to delivery safety and risk engineering solutions to our diverse range of projects including Renewables, Datacentres, Defence, Oil and Gas and mining, as well as:

Demonstrate a thorough understanding and knowledge of technical risk issues, applying process safety skills
Support a local team and provide technical direction and guidance to less experienced staff, coaching them to develop their competency
Work with our global capability to identify opportunities for clients to uplift process safety


What are we looking from you?
Alongside your industry experience in similar role, you will also have:

Understanding of Legislation, Regulations and Standards and regulatory approval pathways.
Technical competency in chemical or mechanical engineering to apply creative solutions to complex problems across all infrastructure industries
Delivery of elements of safety management systems and safety cases
Workshop facilitation or scribing through understanding and application of hazard identification and analysis methods
Understanding and application of qualitative and quantitative risk-based studies
Ability to perform systems safety assurance consulting activities in alignment to systems safety assurance requirements.


We value that each of our team members brings something different to Aurecon. We look for people who have had a broad range of experiences throughout their career and can demonstrate how they have worked as part of a team.

How will your future be shaped by us?
Join Aurecon and work at the forefront of innovation and sustainability. We champion inclusivity, flexibility and career growth, supporting you with mentoring, training and wellbeing programs. Make an impact while bringing your whole self to work.

Ready to bring ideas to life? Apply to join us!

We appreciate the interest of our agency partners, however we're not engaging external recruitment support for this opportunity at this stage.

Challenger Limited is an ASX-listed investment management firm managing $123.9 billion in assets (as at 30 June 2025). Life with us is fast moving and always exciting. Together we’re driving to deliver our vision to provide our customers with financial security for a better retirement.

We achieve this goal by providing a work environment where people from diverse backgrounds, with a range of skills and experiences can contribute and succeed.

Valuations Analyst – Sydney 

We’ve created a brand-new role to strengthen how we independently validate private debt pricing  

Sitting alongside the Quant team, you’ll be the control point that keeps pricing accurate, on time, and defensible.  

If you like being the person who spots issues early, gets the detail right, and keeps everyone honest, this is very much your lane. 

We work flexibly from our Sydney CBD Office (Typically 3 days in office, 2 from home). 

About the role  

You will join a high performing team within the COO Office, which is tightly integrated across our investment teams and collaborates with multiple support functions to drive operational precision and agility. 

Operating alongside the Quantitative team, and functioning as an independent control, you will be central to pricing governance, daily unit pricing, and month-end reporting to the Valuation Committee. 

If you thrive on detail, work well to tight deadlines, and enjoy partnering with portfolio managers and external service providers, this role will suit you perfectly. 

What you’ll be across day-to-day 

Daily operations 

Run pre-9:30am checks on private debt pricing and control reports, digging into variances and data mismatches (think static data, curves, odd gaps). 

Handle price-threshold queries from State Street and our PMs as they come up - and keep things moving 

Book and load trades in Charles River, ironing out any trade-reporting issues before they land in someone else’s inbox. 

Flag issues early with a clear read on impact to unit pricing quality and SLA delivery. 

Month-end and governance: 

Pull together clean, reconciled packs for PMs and the Valuation Committee — and present the private debt reporting. 

Make sure final unit pricing reflects every required valuation within the deadlines. 

Present private debt price reporting to the Valuation Committee and implement directed pricing in internal systems. 

Support semi-annual sensitivity work and any ad-hoc pricing investigations. 

Technical / financial work: 

Maintain and troubleshoot models and reporting using advanced Excel (Power Query, macros, formulas). 

Apply foundational fixed-income knowledge across pricing, derivatives, and cash-flow discounting. 

Skills & experience you will need

You’ve got middle-office or fixed-income operations experience (bank, asset manager, investment admin) and ideally have exposure to private debt instruments. 

As well as;  

Comfort working under strict SLAs and regulatory oversight.  

Experience supporting governance processes (e.g. Valuation Committees) is advantageous 

Advanced Excel skills - (Power Query, macros), data querying and reconciliation. 

Your eye for detail is sharp, and you’re the kind of person who won’t move on until the numbers tie out. 

You communicate clearly, partner well with busy stakeholders, and know when to push back. 

Qualifications 

Bachelor’s degree in finance, Accounting, Economics or equivalent. 

Additional Information 

At Challenger, we’re small enough to be agile, but big enough to accelerate bold ideas. We support your growth and development, offering flexibility and a culture that values your unique contributions. 

Competitive discretionary bonus scheme 

18 weeks paid parental leave for all new parents 

Challenger Day – one extra day off every year in recognition of the effort our people make.  

Additional support leave (fertility, gender affirmation) 

Extra superannuation contributions 

Employee share plan 

Employee Assistance Programme 

Subsidised on-site café and central location near Martin Place Metro 

Access to free onsite yoga, mindfulness and Pilates classes. 

Access to annual free flu shots. 

https://www.challenger.com.au/about-us/careers/our-benefits

Senior Data & Reporting Analyst (6-Month Contract) - Critical Utility Asset Optimisation



The Opportunity & Details
An exciting 6-month contract opportunity has arisen for a highly skilled Senior Data and Reporting Analyst to join a critical Asset Management Optimisation Project within a complex, regulated utility environment.


Contract Rate: $1,000.00 - $1,100.00 per day (Inclusive of Superannuation)

Contract Duration: 6 months, with a strong likelihood of extension based on project needs and performance.

Location: Home-based / Flexible, with compulsory interstate travel to a dedicated operational location one week per month for the duration (all travel and accommodation expenses covered).

This is a high-impact role where your expertise in data analysis, visualisation, and reporting will directly drive strategic and operational decisions in a sector where reliability and compliance are paramount.




Your Responsibilities
As the Senior Data and Reporting Analyst, you will be crucial in translating complex data into actionable business intelligence, both remotely and on-site:


Data Strategy & Quality: Lead the collection, quality assurance, cleansing, and integration of complex data streams from multiple platforms (including asset management systems) specific to a utility or heavily regulated environment.

BI Development: Design, develop, and administer strategic and tactical reports, dashboards, and advanced visualisation/alerting mechanisms using Tableau Desktop and Server.

Technical Expertise: Write and optimize complex queries using Oracle SQL to support data extraction, performance tuning, and integrity across the reporting environment.

Stakeholder Engagement: Proactively liaise with business unit stakeholders to gather requirements, analyse and improve processes, and deliver data-driven insights.

Process Improvement: Identify and implement opportunities for continuous improvement, process automation, and the integration of paper-based forms into digital workflows.



Essential Skills and Experience
To be successful in this contract, you must demonstrate:


Critical Industry Experience: Demonstrated and recent experience working in a complex, regulated multi-utility environment (e.g., Water, Power, Gas, or similar heavy infrastructure) is critical.

Travel Readiness: Unrestricted ability and willingness to travel interstate to a dedicated operational site for one week per month for the entire 6-month contract duration.

Proven Seniority: Extensive experience in data cleansing, manipulating complex datasets, and ensuring data integrity in dynamic, large-scale environments.

Tableau Expert: Essential proficiency in Tableau Desktop for creating interactive dashboards and reports, and experience with Tableau Server for publishing and managing performance.

SQL Mastery: Strong expertise in Oracle SQL for writing complex queries, advanced joins, and performance tuning.



Highly Desirable Assets
Familiarity with Power BI (including data modelling and DAX) or a strong willingness to cross-skill.

Prior experience working with IBM Maximo or similar Asset Management systems for data extraction and integration.



Apply Now
If you are a resourceful, high-performing Senior Analyst with critical utility sector experience and are fully prepared for the compulsory monthly interstate travel, we encourage you to apply today for this excellent contract opportunity with a competitive daily rate and strong possibility of extension!


Please contact Joseph Demetriou () for a confidential discussion about the role.

Ad Text:
Why work for Neumann Steel?
You would be working for one of the most reputable family owned and operated companies first established on the Gold Coast over 50 years ago. We specialise in steel reinforcing and plastic accessory products in the QLD and NSW markets. Our highly integrated supply chain is supported by our experienced staff and a wealth of industry knowledge.
  
With a people-first mindset, Neumann Steel is dedicated to supporting the local community and fostering long-lasting relationships while delivering quality commercial and residential projects in the spirit of openness and honesty. We strive to build a rewarding, inclusive, and inspiring culture, with innovation at the forefront of mind.




Quick overview of the role 
We are currently seeking an experienced Data Analyst to join our ICT team in a full-time capacity.  This role is responsible for the architect and implementation of a scalable data warehouse, consolidating data from multiple sources. This position is based at our Currumbin Head Office on the Gold Coast.

What will you be doing?

Develop and maintain PowerBI reports that provide clear, actionable insights for each business unit.
Collaborate with stakeholders to define reporting requirements and ensure alignment with business objectives.
Automate data refresh processes and optimise performance for real-time analytics
Design and implement automated workflows using Power Automate to streamline data processes and reporting.
Integrate Power Platform solutions with other Microsoft and third-party systems (e.g. SharePoint, Dynamics 365, Teams)
Provide ongoing support, training and documentation for end-users and team members.
Maintain up-to-date knowledge of Power platforms features, updates and bet practices.
Collaborate with Data Partners, Product Champions and project teams to promote adoption of data standards.
Document data models, ETL processes and reporting standards.
Analyse business/system processes using various methods such as gap analysis or PDCA to find opportunities for improvement, via reporting dashboards and automation.



What are we looking for in the successful candidate?

Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, Business Analytics, or related field (or equivalent experience).
Strong experience in data engineering, data analysis, and analytics projects, including Microsoft Fabric, SQL Server, ETL tools, DAX, T-SQL, and performance optimisation.
Advanced SQL skills and solid understanding of data architecture, data warehousing, and Azure cloud technologies.
Proven ability to analyse complex business processes, identify inefficiencies, and translate requirements into technical solutions (automation, reporting, dashboards).
Skilled in Power BI, Power Automate, Power Apps, and workflow automation; MS Power BI and Power Automate certifications preferred.
Experience collaborating with both business and technical teams, with strong communication, stakeholder management, and documentation skills.
Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines, DevOps, Microsoft 365 (SharePoint, Teams, Outlook), scripting languages (PowerShell, JavaScript), and agile methodologies.

What’s in it for you

Free parking onsite
Free lunch on Friday’s!
Mental health and wellbeing support, wellness discounts for mind, body, work, and life, including an Employee Assistance Program

Our culture is driven by our values. We value high performance, collaboration, innovation, integrity and respect. Working for us means being part of a great team of people and we believe our people are our biggest asset. If you think you would be able to complement our awesome team, then we’d like to hear from you.

Join a leading Australian financial institution and help uplift enterprise-wide model risk management.

Are you passionate about quantitative modelling, risk management, and ensuring models support high-quality business decisions? We are seeking a Senior Associate, Enterprise Validation to join a high-performing Model Risk team and contribute to ongoing improvements in model governance, analytics, and validation practices.

About the Role

As a Senior Associate in Enterprise Validation, you’ll play a critical role in assessing and validating the models that drive decision-making across the organisation. You’ll collaborate with model developers, risk specialists, and senior stakeholders to ensure models are robust, compliant, and aligned to internal risk policies.

This role suits someone with strong analytical capability, hands-on modelling experience, and a passion for enhancing model risk outcomes within a complex environment.

Key Responsibilities

Validate high-materiality models, including reporting, rating assignment, and remediation recommendations.

Provide advisory support and challenge on model risk to business stakeholders.

Identify and assess model health issues and recommend improvements.

Conduct independent reviews of existing models and identify opportunities for uplift.

Support and maintain the model validation activity pipeline.

Share knowledge and guide team members where required.

Contribute to the enhancement of model validation processes, frameworks, and broader model risk management activities.

About You

You bring a strong quantitative foundation and practical experience developing or validating models in financial, academic, or analytical environments.

Essential Skills:

3+ years’ experience in financial risk, quantitative modelling, or model validation.

Experience building or validating statistical or mathematical models.

Strong analytical capability and understanding of risk management principles.

Proficiency with Excel, SAS, SQL, R, or Python.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills.

Strong organisational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities.

Graduate degree in a quantitative field (Mathematics, Statistics, Finance, Engineering, etc.).

Master’s or PhD highly regarded.

Desirable:

Experience within large financial institutions or regulated environments.

Familiarity with model risk management frameworks and validation methodologies.

Ability to influence stakeholders and support continuous improvement initiatives.

Exposure to cross-functional teams such as model development, audit, risk, or finance.

Why This Opportunity?

Be part of a leading institution known for strong risk culture and analytical excellence.

Contribute to high-impact, enterprise-level model risk initiatives.

Join a collaborative team of quantitative and risk professionals.

Hybrid working environment.

Strong career development pathways within risk, modelling, and analytics.

About e&e

e&e is a professional Business and Technology Consultancy providing services to our clients during business initiation, transformation and IT programs of work. e&e are partners and trusted advisors to some of the largest corporations and institutions across Australia. 

e&e is currently engaged with some of Australia's most exciting ICT projects across a diverse range of industries such as utilities, financial services, resources, mining, healthcare and government sectors. e&e's management team are dedicated to developing and recognising its staff by providing a dynamic working environment and career progression within an organisation that is innovative and continuing to experience growth across Australia.

The Opportunity

We currently have opportunities available within our organisation for a Systems Analyst to join our consulting team.

You will be working with project and technology teams contributing to a range of activities from implementing new systems, building new system features and improving the existing applications & platforms at varying levels of maturity.

To join our team, you will demonstrate:

At least 5 years Systems Analysis experience within a complex Enterprise Level environment.

Assisting in documenting business needs to ensure correct definition, communication, and delivery of technology projects

Document business requirements using standardised formats and requirements management tools for clear and consistent communication.

Conduct gap analysis and impact assessments for new features, system changes, and integrations.

Serve as a liaison between business clients and technical staff, translating business needs into functional and non-functional requirements.

Translate business needs into clear user stories, process flows, data models, and solution specifications.

Work with business stakeholders to understand problems and opportunities; impacts and outcomes

Continuously improve processes and procedures to optimize efficiency and effectiveness

Ability to lead and facilitate workshops.

Collaborative consultative approach to your work.

If you are looking for an exciting and diverse new engagement, with the ability to expand your industry and project experience, please click apply or send an email through to info@eeitsolutions.com.au
